---
title: Thai Style Yellow Cod Curry With Spinach & Jasmine Rice
description: They grow a lot of coconuts in Indonesia and love to cook with them. The country's food is often spicy but the heat is offset with sweetness from the coconuts and often a sour note too. We're attempting this balancing act in today's curry. The sauce bathing the veggies should be hot, sharp and sweet. Top it all off with golden toasted cashews and the herbal notes of coriander.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/thai-style-yellow-cod-curry-1ebe9d3f-ee0829c6.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/thai-style-yellow-cod-curry-5f3cf5a1b641f71ef95eed6b-f4159443.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/thai-style-yellow-cod-curry-5f3cf5a1b641f71ef95eed6b
author: Michael Steadman
course: main course
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: Thai
nutrition:
  calories: 589 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 2 g
  protein: 31 g
  sodium: 2.1 g
  serving size: 580
servings: 2
---

Pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When
boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, lower the heat to
medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove
the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another
~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Chop the @Cod Fillets{2} into 2cm chunks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw fish.

When the rice has been cooking for 5 mins, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a
medium saucepan on medium-high heat. When hot add the @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45%g}
and cook stirring frequently until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add the @Coconut Milk{200%ml},
@Vegetable Stock Powder{1%tsp} and @Water for the Curry{100%ml}. Bring to the boil and
turn down to simmer. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the curry has simmered for ~{5%minutes}, add the cod pieces, making sure they
are fully submerged in the sauce. Simmer until cooked through, a further
~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when it is opaque in the middle.

Add the @Baby Spinach{100%g} to the curry, pop a lid on and cook the curry for
~{3-4%minutes} until spinach is fully wilted. Meanwhile, zest and halve your
@Lime{1/2}. Once cooked, add a squeeze of lime juice into the curry and gently
stir through, season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Cut the
remaining lime into wedges.

Carefully fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and mix through the lime zest. Share
between your plates and top with the cod curry. Serve any remaining lime wedges
alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!